  "explanation": "In determining the sentence, the court considers that the defendant is a first-time offender with no prior criminal record, which weightily mitigates the severity of the punishment. While the embezzlement of $25,000 represents a significant breach of fiduciary duty and trust, the defendant's proactive efforts to partially repay the stolen funds demonstrate a degree of remorse and accountability. The motive of debt repayment, while not an excuse, further suggests the act was not driven by professional malice or complex racketeering. The outburst from the spectator has no bearing on the legal determination of the sentence. A custodial sentence of 6 months reflects the seriousness of the crime while acknowledging the defendant's mitigate circumstances and lack of criminal history.",
  "verdict": 6
}
